<%- include('header'); -%>
<div class='row'>
	<div class='col'>
		<h2>Testing Page</h2>
		<p>This page allows the user to perform various tests on their browser. It will allow them to discern any sound throughput issues.</p>
		<p>Sound issues can happen at any stage in the audio pipeline, from the creation of the sound in the library to the individual audio jack that is
		responsible for sending the audio to the speakers or headphones. This test will first try to determine any discrepancies in audio representation in different
		browsers and media players.</p>
		<p>On completion of the test, the results will be logged to the database and compared with the average for your browser.</p>

		<h2>Pitch Variance Test</h2>
		<p>This test is responsible for logging the pitch limits of audio hardware, whether that be on the listening hardware or in the device.</p>
		<button class='btn' id='beginBtn' onclick='begin()'>Begin Test</button>
		<div id='testArea' class='row'>
		</div>

		<h2>Audio Inversion Test</h2>
		<p>Inverts audio using a software filter. Audio should be cancelled out</p>
		<button class='btn' id='beginBtn2' onclick='beginInversion()'>Begin Test</button>
		<div id='testAreaInversion' class='row'>
		</div>

		<h2>Filter Chaining Test</h2>
		<p>Chains together semantically identical audio filters and tests if they sound the same.</p>
		<button class='btn' id='beginBtn3' onclick='beginChain()'>Begin Test</button>
		<div id='testAreaChain' class='row'>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<script src="js/main.js"></script>
<script src="js/test.js"></script>
<%- include('footer'); -%>
